-- Audit filing: docs/notes/audit/audit-spa-history-lessons-2026-06-10.md
-- Twenty new open/future items + one refs row each (kind=design-note; the
-- refs.kind enum has no 'audit' value — existing precedent reuses design-note,
-- flagged in the audit doc §5 per ADR-0002 Rule 7).
BEGIN;

INSERT INTO items (id, title, description, state, disposition, scope, tier) VALUES
('multi-writer-slots-get-owners',
 'Give the un-owned multi-writer slots owners (board write, blind-mode prefs, store.engine)',
 $$Staged per audit §3.7: (1) move the analysis-service.ts:463 maxVisitsTarget write behind the early-return guards AND through mutateBoard (it fires even when analyzeRange refuses the query; the un-bumped write misses the debounced sync until an unrelated mutation fires one) and delete the unjustified cast. (2) Blind-mode owner in the review session: snapshot/restore a supplied list of session-UI pref keys (showMoveSuggestions, treeExpanded) on loadCard/finishCard/endSession/abort; showMoveSuggestions is persisted (session.ui rides buildPersistencePayload), so the current force-true clobber survives reloads; whether finishCard's reveal is deliberate pedagogy is a maintainer call — likely fix shape: restore at endSession, preserve the reveal at finishCard. (3) Extract an engine-connection owner module named for the problem class (connect/disconnect-reset/info/selection/metrics), collapsing the duplicated reset (~:169-192 vs ~:398-411; 19 direct store.engine.* assignments, incl. bypassing setSelectedModel at :192/:408); makes store.engine + owner a wholesale-replaceable unit (fork-relevant) and is the natural landing for engine-connection-lifecycle-logout. (4) Data-driven ESLint writer-enumeration rule ({subtree -> owners} config map) with ADR-0001's template-toggle exception carved out; record as an ADR-0001 amendment per Rule 6. Run hack-rationalization-detector out-of-frame before calling any leg done (>1-writer state).$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'medium'),
('migration-leaf-assertion-and-composition-test',
 'Migration fail-loud guard: independent-witness leaf assertions + the composition-level invariant test',
 $$Audit §3.13. The 47->48 F-optimizer retirement walked a wrong optional-chained blob path, silently no-oped, and stamped v48 (caught pre-ship; repair migration 48->49). The test gap was NOT a vacuous fixture: no per-migration fixtures existed for 44->56 at all, while the test-file header still claims one describe block per migration (fix the header). Two legs: (a) the composition-level invariant test — hydrate a legacy blob through migrate + updateFromRemote + save, compare key sets against a clean migration; verified absent from the suite; this is the load-bearing half. (b) A leaf-assertion helper for ACTIVE migration bodies only, with an independent witness (assert against the path the runtime actually reads / realistic fixtures), else it conditions out on the same wrong path; authored instance-free in the B1 framework portion; the helper itself must be frozen-once-shipped or inlined, or it becomes a mutable dependency of frozen bodies. Bump-cadence relaxation (~1.38/day) is explicitly out of scope (ADR-level; audit §7.5). See docs/notes/design/migration-test-rotation-plan.md (its Open Question 1 names the co-tested-fixture hazard).$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('branded-path-types',
 'Brand RootToLeafPath / RootToCurrentPath and execute the deferred call-site audit + mid-tree fixture',
 $$Audit §3.4. Three shipped fixes in the May match arc (d62b51d, ec4cb3d, 59365c8) plus a fourth audit-found instance (87fbc3f) and a documented still-latent twin in playEngineMoves (deep-clone only in playEngineMatch; usePlayFromPosition.ts:565). The brand half deliberately revisits a recorded ADR-0003 N=3 deferral (postmortem §5b / worklog 2026-05-15) whose threshold is argued effectively met; the call-site audit (16 files call getActiveVariationPath) and the fixture leg (no test constructs current != leaf) were unconditional recommendations and stand cleanly. Mint brands next to NodeId in the identifier vocabulary (NOT engine/), add IDENTIFIERS.md rows, keep the review-session state-machine surface path-type-free, adopt the explicit-position-parameter rule. Brands on arrays are lost through slice/concat — mint-site helpers re-brand. Precedent: dd3b85e (zero-runtime brand retrofit, 817 tests green).$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'medium'),
('hydration-rebind-residue-audit',
 'Close the module-scope-vs-hydration audit residue and name the failure class',
 $$Audit §3.9 (deflated from "never executed": the 2026-06-03 knowntags consult swept the boot path — 7 sites, 1 hazard fixed structurally — and the board-scope audit covered module-scope surfaces). Honest residue: useQueryTelemetry's reconnect-rebind contract, the thumbnail caches' hydration axis, analysis-service's per-board interaction-time rebind; plus one short doc naming the failure shape (one-shot binding vs hydration/identity, two distinct axes) and indexing the existing nets (immediate:true watchers, disjoint write targets / 5b57d25, IDENTITY_SCOPED_CACHES, ProfileState user-authored-only invariant). A general whenHydrated() barrier was DELIBERATELY DECLINED 2026-06-03 ("build the gate only if a second genuine instance appears") — engage that decision on its own terms; barrier/lint conditional on audit findings. Record each audited site's ADR-0003 band so the output doubles as the fork's hydration-coupled-state inventory.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('cast-hygiene-lint',
 'Mechanize the cast-justification rule: ban bare `as any`, then justification-adjacency for all casts',
 $$Audit §3.10. The review-only rule held at ~50% in a 32-of-224 sample. Stage 1: stock ESLint ban on bare `as any` (~13 code sites; could go straight to error per existing zero-or-triaged adoption practice). Stage 2: custom justification-adjacency rule for all casts (~200-280 sites; measure first per a75814c; local-rule precedent exists in frontend/eslint-rules/). This RE-OPENS a recorded deferral — eslint.config.js:134-138 parks no-explicit-any as "warn-as-backlog, not adopted here" — and the rule-rationale header must record that relationship (ADR-0002 Rule 6). Escape hatch is the established vue/no-v-html model (disable-next-line + justification). Fork reshape: justification comments on band boundaries name the cast's band character, so the inventory doubles as the seam map; count the `as unknown as` brand-strip shape as a follow-on ratchet target. SFC template casts were unaudited — measure them too.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('typed-capability-metadata-mirror',
 'Type the per-capability proxy metadata mirror; validate once at the version-response boundary',
 $$Audit §3.2. capabilities is Record<string, Record<string, unknown>> on BOTH the query side (engine/katago/types.ts:276) and the advertisement twin (:485 — the side the casts read via store.engine.info.capabilities); available_value_bindings is read through casts at capability-injection.ts:203 (`as readonly string[]`, unjustified) and AnalysisControls.vue:48 (guarded). The learned-vf dispatch (line 150) presupposed an AdaptiveReevaluateCapability type that never existed. Declare per-capability metadata interfaces at the mirror, validated once in version-probe.ts::parseVersionResponse (existing cast-free, unit-tested seam); mismatched KNOWN capability degrades that capability loudly (level 4/5) — must NOT extend the connection-refusal surface (reserved for missing delta_analysis per the dispatch) — and unknown capability NAMES keep passing through. Adjacent doc debt: the learned-vf dispatch still reads Status: Open though shipped; note a status edit in the implementing PR.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('services-boundary-deny-by-default',
 'Invert the component-to-service ESLint boundary to deny-by-default; file the ADR-0010 Revisit #4 tension as work',
 $$Audit §3.11. The enumerated blocklist (eslint.config.js:166-179, exactly four services) was incomplete from day one (sync-service, qeubo-service, api-client, resource-service never listed — all predate the list) and is fail-open by shape; the rationale census at :81-86 is stale since 35c939c (2026-06-01). Step (a): restrict src/services/** from components wholesale; exempt the reactive-state class {analysis-ledger, analysis-config, stability-trajectory-store} via one named constant (REACTIVE_STATE_EXEMPTIONS) whose comment marks it as the provisional form of a future state/ directory; use @typescript-eslint/no-restricted-imports for allowTypeImports; measure first. Known adjudications: AnalysisControls.vue:17 type-only import from pure analysis-bundle; the layering tenet covers App.vue but the glob does not, and App.vue:30 imports analysisService today — widen the glob or name the gap explicitly. Refresh the census header with at-adoption historical phrasing. Step (b), separate sign-off arc: relocate the reactive-state modules to state/, recording the machinery-vs-payload seam (ledger machinery band-agnostic, payload Go) in headers + FILES.md; rule becomes directory-structural and the constant dissolves. This item is also the work-status record ADR-0010 Revisit #4 has lacked.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('keyed-cache-brand-at-construction',
 'Construction-time rule: new keyed caches mint branded keys declaring the value''s dependency set',
 $$Audit §3.5. The under-keyed composite-cache class is proven (ledger palette-swap stranding + same-day twin in stability-trajectory-store; both closed by the 2026-06-08 brand arc); discovery was reactive each time. The bounded r:/e: prefix audit is ALREADY ANSWERED SAFE (verification: mint only in projectLedgerToBundle, parse only in replayBundleIntoLedger; legacy DJB2-hex/'default' values cannot start with r:/e:) — deliverable is recording that conclusion in the analysis-bundle prefix note + IDENTIFIERS.md rows. Then codify in frontend/CLAUDE.md's Type-driven-design section + a pre-merge-checklist line (a checklist line is G4-shaped mitigation, not a fix — the RCA's own caveat): any new keyed cache mints a branded key whose declaration names the dependency set of the value; each key leg carries a one-word band call (domain-bound vs agnostic) in its IDENTIFIERS.md row. Optional later: a best-effort lint flagging multi-variable template-literal Map keys.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('work-status-authoring-hygiene',
 'Harvest dangling prose deferrals into the store; refs rows to paid-for diagnoses; item-id-or-declined convention',
 $$Audit §3.22 ([raise] hint). One bounded pass over the miners' compiled dangling-deferral lists (appendix §1: worklog-current findings 1-5, worklog-2026-05 finding 5, worklog-2026-04 finding 1, retros 1-2, postmortems 3): file / drop-with-dated-record / confirm-done. Add refs rows pointing pv-hover-jank-range-query and many-boards-open-slowness at docs/notes/audit/perf-audit-nav-and-pv-hover-2026-05-27.md, noting cause #1 shipped as perf-fix3 so the residual is causes C.2/C.3; re-profile BOTH symptoms before building levers (the dropped rb3-packet-receive-chunking item records why: ~99ms re-measured vs ~2.35s attributed). Convention going forward: every deferral/postmortem-recommendation bullet ends with an item id or a grep-able 'not-filed: <reason>' marker; items filed near a diagnosis doc get a refs row at filing; retitle open items to their residuals on next touch. Fork reshape: band-annotate open frontend items in extra jsonb during the pass; never drop a generalization-rationale deferral on single-domain grounds. Surface spa-board-scope-consistency-audit status as a maintainer question (audit §7.4).$$,
 'open', 'future', 'umbrella', 'medium'),
('doc-graph-dangling-signal-cleanup',
 'De-noise the doc-graph dangling-reference report so genuine drift is reviewable',
 $$Audit §3.24 ([raise] hint). 83 of 125 live danglers (~66%) are noise by the project's own conventions: 55 worklog-origin (the consolidation note classifies worklogs frozen, and even asserts the report already segregates them — currently false; generate.mjs:833-835 segregates docs/archive/** only), 28 more target the retired deferred-items hub, ~25 from executed playbooks under the fuller convention. In tools/doc-graph/generate.mjs: (a) align the frozen boundary with the working convention — maintainer confirms the classification (audit §7.6); (b) split dangling classes: missing-on-disk vs outside-node-set (four on-disk files are currently reported with the same wording as deleted ones: frontend/tests/CLAUDE.md, backend/samples/README.md, backend/qeubo/README.md, frontend/docs/i18n.md); directory links are structurally skipped (BACKTICK_PATH_RE requires .md); (c) tombstone handling for retired hubs. Then an advisory no-new-danglers ratchet as a report section (gate history counsels advisory-first). Separately fix two verified stale code-side pointers: ADR-0010:169 cites tests/integration/render-locality/ (actual render-count/; ADR amendment convention applies) and MoveSuggestions.vue:144 cites the pre-reorg audit path. Generator change alters report structure -> regenerate in the same PR. Umbrella scope.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'umbrella', 'medium'),
('code-comment-stable-handles',
 'Code comments cite stable handles, not counts/censuses/ad-hoc numbers',
 $$Audit §3.25. Decayed instances: store/index.ts:331 "Four cleanups" over eleven actual operations (one unenumerated); eslint.config.js:81-86 census asserting violations resolved 2026-06-01; O12-O15 docstring tags extending a frozen archived plan's numbering and colliding with all four of its definitions (O1-O5 match; plan path cite at :416 is also stale — actual docs/archive/notes/resource-ownership-audit-plan.md). Fix: additive descriptive slugs alongside the O-numbers (never edit the frozen plan); the two census fixes ride with the scoped-state and services-boundary items. Convention lands as a REFINEMENT of frontend/CLAUDE.md's resource-ownership prescription item 4 (a parallel convention would be the ADR-0005 Rule 1 failure it decries): prefer repo-resident handles (slugs, committed-doc anchors, registry labels, test names); a work-status id always travels with a descriptive slug so handles resolve in any clone/fork without the maintainer's DB; counts live in registries/tests/generated reports.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('enrichment-merge-null-validation',
 'Validate, don''t coerce, at the enrichment merge boundary (mergeRecords inner-null edge)',
 $$Audit §3.6. The adaptive-deeper postmortem's §5.5 sharp edge (a non-null inner object with null-bearing fields replaces a populated leaf wholesale) is still unguarded at analysis-ledger.ts mergeRecords ~:185-195, and the 2026-06-08 stratification WIDENED exposure by removing the visit gate from the enrichment merge path. Guard is structural and instance-blind inside the Band-1 helper (object-typed incoming value whose own values include null/undefined AND replacing a populated leaf -> structured loud-warn, caller-supplied label/escalation); scope to the nested-record call site (state; deltas/cwt are numeric leaves already covered); all KataGo calibration lives at the Go-typed call sites. Terminal loudness level decided at implementation between levels 3-4 — a throw inside recordEnrichment for a wire-origin anomaly is probably wrong. mergeEnrichment is already unit-exercised (analysis-ledger-stratified.test.ts) so the null-bearing fixture has a home. ADR-0002 grounding is the general decision text; Rule 4 by analogy (post-ACL services layer). Low urgency; no observed incident in normal operation.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('vue-lifecycle-footgun-guards',
 'Mechanize the two expressible Vue footguns: boolean gate-prop defaults; module-intent state in <script setup>',
 $$Audit §3.12. Five paid-for investigations; the two costliest share a signature: correct-looking code whose scope/default silently differs from intent, latent until a second consumer with a different lifecycle arrives. (1) Boolean gate-props: omission casts to false (4756c30's "other consumers safe" claim falsified by 69810e2); vue-tsc cannot police this even in principle (omission is type-legal); assess eslint-plugin-vue's require-default-prop / no-boolean-default first (unadopted; config deliberately avoids the broad preset); key any custom rule on name patterns (active/enabled/visible), never component allowlists; generalize the omitted-prop rendering test that already exists for BaseChart (BaseChart-collapsed-gate.test.ts) into a reusable helper. (2) Module-intent mutable state declared in <script setup> is per-instance (MiniBoardCanvas texture flash, 463a15e; its plain-<script> fix is the worked example); trigger on module-intent, not all top-level state (per-instance non-reactive state is legitimate — cached dims). (3) One checked frontend/CLAUDE.md section folding in the RESIDUE lessons only (v-memo key-stability under churning shallowRef; container-query self-styling; structuredClone vs reactive Proxy), cross-linking ADR-0010's corollary rather than restating it. Each guard ships verified against its original defect. Complements thumbnail-render-lifecycle-consolidation (which covers the thumbnail surface architecturally).$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'medium'),
('adr-record-amendments-2026-06',
 'Record the fired ADR triggers (0001 #2; 0003 #1+#2 with the fork-axis re-cut); strip ADR-0010''s artifact',
 $$Audit §3.23. Bounded amendments per the project's convention (read ADR-0005 end to end first; append, don't silently edit): (1) ADR-0001 — record trigger #2 as fired; correct the mutator-benefits enumeration scoped to mutateBoard only (the re-wrap bullet at lines ~99-103 is stale for render reasons; mutateReviewSession still identity-swaps at store/index.ts:209; the version-counter/invariant/grep bullets hold); fix the Related-section docstring claim and the stale audit path in the mutator comment. (2) ADR-0003 — record trigger #1 as fired TWICE (chess-clone active; the generic knowledge flash-card fork, 2026-06-09/10) and trigger #2; delegate only the per-file inventory listing to FILES.md, RETAINING the band definitions, the band-mixed seam analysis, and the port-sizing prose; add a non-game fork sizing beside the Chess one with B2 marked SPLIT (game-tree skeleton replaced; SR-orchestration flow and generic charting kept), not "replace"; re-key FILES.md's three legend lines to the any-knowledge-domain criterion (78 B1/39 B2/97 B3/1 B? at HEAD); note the useReviewSession ADR-vs-FILES.md band disagreement (trigger #3 instance). (3) ADR-0010 — delete the two trailing harness-envelope artifact lines (present since creation, survived three edits) with a one-line amendment note + a CI grep for harness-envelope strings under docs/. (4) Fold the trigger-sweep checklist into the parent item as cadence (re-derive the trigger count from end-to-end reads; the "38" figure is miner-internal). docs/adr-synopsis.md co-changes (the cochange advisory flags it); docs/handoff-current.md's chess-keyed Domain-extension prose is touched by the same change; doc-graph regeneration in the same PR.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'umbrella', 'small'),
('resource-service-calibration-seam',
 'Invert resource-service: export the generic verb; move Go calibration orchestration to the B3 side',
 $$Audit §3.18. services/resource-service.ts is a named Band-1 module whose ONLY public verb is Go-specific: loadVisitDistribution (:53) fetches as fetchResource<any> (:55) and hands to the [B3] intensity factory, while the generic fetchResource<T> (:40) is module-private. The typed boundary half-exists already: engine/suggestion-colors.ts exports VisitDistributionData (:40) and the typed setVisitDistribution (:211); initializeIntensityFactory (:231) is a back-compat alias — so the <any> discards a published type one import away, and the orchestration likely lands in suggestion-colors itself (no new module). Export getResource<T>; move fetch+initialize+the hue-shift watch (useAppBootstrap.ts:116-120) into one B3 init invoked from the bootstrap via a single named domain-init call. Preserve the documented ordering tolerance (immediate watch; fire-and-forget catch at :408-409; corroborated by the 2026-06-03 consult Part 2 row 2). Bootstrap limb deflated: useAppBootstrap is band-mixed through three other imports regardless — retag it honestly as wiring (App.vue precedent) in the same PR. Verification: manual cold-start smoke of the suggestion-color gradient (no automated coverage).$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('rehome-agnostic-utils-engine-util',
 'Re-home generateUUID + updateRegistry (with private setDeep) from engine/util.ts to lib/',
 $$Audit §3.19. Two domain-free exports stranded in [B3] engine/util.ts drag false B3 edges onto agnostic consumers, including the generic registry write path: cross-band edges from useQeubo.ts:87 [B1], archived-migrations.ts:29 [B1], SettingsTab.vue:35 [B2]; same-band importers board-factory.ts:14, useDirtyBoardGuard.ts:41, sgf-loader.ts:5 also re-point. setDeep has zero external consumers (private helper; may fold into updateRegistry). Land in lib/utils.ts — its FILES.md:316 row is itself stale ("the only inhabitant": actually debounce, isObject, deepMerge; fix the row). VERIFIED NON-COLLAPSE: setDeep silently creates intermediates / accepts any value; lib/knobs.ts's walkers deliberately throw on missing parents and accept finite numbers only — different ADR-0002 calibrations; co-locate, never merge. archived-migrations.ts:29 is an import-block line, outside the bodies-only freeze — header-level edit, no shim, with a one-line justification in the PR. Refresh the stale prose cites (board-factory.ts:26-33, AnalysisTabsEditor.vue:14, generateUUID's own docstring) and tests/unit/engine/util.test.ts in the same motion. Bonus drift for the ADR amendment item: ADR-0003:180-181 describes "captures math" the file no longer contains.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small'),
('keybindings-substrate-catalog-split',
 'Split lib/keybindings.ts: generic registry substrate vs the Go-shaped action catalog',
 $$Audit §3.16. The [B1]-tagged file fuses domain-free machinery (effectiveKey, normalizeKey) with a catalog whose handlers dispatch analysisService/useNavigation/store writes. The REAL work is two seams verification exposed: the enabledWhen vocabulary ('activeBoardExists'/'engineConnected') is baked into the substrate's types (:55-58) and isActionEnabled reads the store directly (:306-312) — parameterize as catalog-supplied predicates or a host-capability interface; and validateKeybindingsRegistry closes over KEYBINDINGS_REGISTRY (:326) — must take the registry as a parameter (useAppBootstrap's call site changes shape). CONFIRMED: action ids are threaded through persisted state (store.profile.settings.keybindings) — pure code motion, id strings unchanged, no schema bump. Five importers; catalog band is mixed (nav.* B2, ponder/overlay B3-flavored) — single tag + values-note per the timing.ts precedent (FILES.md:315) is acceptable. Ride-alongs: stale Phase-1 header claim at :31-36 (Phase 2 shipped); stale design-note paths in both file headers (plan moved to docs/archive/notes/design/). The cheap retag-only alternative forfeits the substrate's B1 discoverability — that discoverability is the argument for the split.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'medium'),
('review-scoring-named-seam',
 'Extract per-move delta scoring from useReviewSession into a named engine-band function',
 $$Audit §3.17. ADR-0003 designed this seam in prose ("the orchestration is portable; the scoring extraction is not", :193-196) and names useReviewSession as the Revisit #3 canary — which has tripped: ADR says Band 2 (:149-152), FILES.md:229 tags [B3]. Extract the per-color extra.{color}.deltas indexing with the s_1-fast-path-then-path-scan lookup (:471-508) plus the ADR-0002 loud-failure branch (:510-529) into engine/analysis/review-scoring.ts taking an ENRICHMENT ACCESSOR as a parameter — the engine band is currently services-clean (verified zero engine->services imports); importing the ledger would create the first such edge; the accessor matches ADR-0003's takes-the-predicate-as-a-parameter idiom (:233-234). Tier-1 tests for the indexing and scan-order fallback become possible (scan order is load-bearing per inline comments; behavior drift is the hazard — existing tier-3 + e2e harness are the net). The extraction names the FIRST of ~4 Go seams in the file (sgf.parse loadCard, applyGoMove capture, gtpToBoard follow-through remain) — annotate band-mixed, don't retag clean. Scope discipline: the review-session-state-split cohesion question is separate; don't grow the PR past the seam. Record as evidence on refactoring-queue-adr0007.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'medium'),
('band-conformance-ci-check',
 'Mechanize ADR-0003 band conformance: CI check that FILES.md band tags are consistent with import bands',
 $$Audit §3.14. ADR-0003 names its own weakness ("the principle is policy, not mechanism") and ADR-0002 Rule 7 already names band tags as a fail-loudly-governed closed vocabulary — this is that rule's mechanization. A doc-graph-style Node script parsing FILES.md tags + the import graph, enforcing band(file) >= band(import), [B?] exempt, annotated-exception list framed as encoding FILES.md's dominant-concern legend rule (expected non-empty by design). DESIGN DECISIONS FOUND BY VERIFICATION: (a) the literal rule drowns — ~37 additional [B1] files violate via the two band-mixed hubs (store/index.ts [B3], types.ts [B2]); scope to B3-leaf/engine imports or exempt hubs explicitly; (b) the checker forces adjudication of recorded FILES.md-vs-ADR-0003 tag disagreements (store/index.ts, analysis-ledger, wait-for-analysis, helper.ts) — that is drift surfacing loudly; (c) MUST fail loudly on rows resolving to no file (FILES.md:45 still lists jquery-bridge.ts, deleted 2026-06-01 in 9949b28) — composes with FILES.md:348-351's own flagged future scripted check; (d) settle type-only/dev-only import policy at adoption (SidebarWidget.vue:13 type-only; main.ts:10 DEV-block). Key on tags, not directory paths (engine/helper.ts is [B1]). Re-key the FILES.md [B1] legend line to the any-domain test at adoption or taggers under-classify. Adopt warn-first against the measured baseline; burn-down list is largely the sibling seam items. Ships with the ADR-0003 amendment noting the structural half became mechanism (content half stays review judgment). Relationship: first concrete per-tenet mechanization under adr-effectiveness-audits' theme.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'medium'),
('reviewcard-canonical-content-rename',
 'Revisit 34b''s retained ReviewCard.sgf: rename the domain field to the wire''s canonical-content vocabulary',
 $$Audit §3.20. REFRAME IS LOAD-BEARING: 34b deliberately retained ReviewCard.sgf as recorded design (34b-frontend-brief.md; 34b-complete-status.md "unchanged, as intended"), premised explicitly on no second-domain consumer — the generic flash-card fork invalidates that premise (ADR-0003 Revisit #1), so this revisits a recorded decision whose trigger fired; it does not "finish" anything. The wire carries canonical_content (types/backend.ts:1133); the ACL re-specializes it at backend-service.ts:125 (sgf: raw.canonical_content). Compiler-driven rename to canonicalContent: ~5 src sites (types.ts:1685, backend-service.ts:125, useReviewSession.ts:251, useDirtyBoardGuard.ts:122, card-tree-echarts.ts:249 — the last delegating to getCardThumbnailSync whose cardSgf param is one more vocabulary site) + ~3 forced test fixtures; e2e seed.ts is optional consistency. Scope crisp for sgf alone: defaultVisits/gamma come from the deliberately-opaque grading blob (out of scope; state this so the scope reads principled). Prose citing the old mapping lives only in frozen archives — carry the supersession note in the types.ts doc comment instead. Content-only doc impact; no doc-graph regen. Cross-ref chess-clone.$$,
 'open', 'future', 'frontend', 'small');

